ce:section.ce:para:
The surface morphology of the Ni-NPs/GCE and Ni-NPs/RCQDs/GCE electrodes was studied by FE-SEM (Fig. 2
                        ). In Fig. 2a one can see the formation of the foliaceous structure of Ni on bare GCE. Further magnifying on this image is seen in Fig. 3
                        b in which several masses are apparent with average diameters of 50–100 nm. These masses are not dispersed so homogenously. However, for Ni-NPs deposited on RCQDs decorated GCE (Fig. 2c and d), a completely different morphology was obtained. As it can be observed, Ni has been deposited as beads in an ordered granular array with nano cracks between grains. The grains are almost homogeneously dispersed on the surface with a size distribution between ca. 30 to 150 nm.
